commit.message: tests/Makefile.am: fix PYTHON_PATH for make distcheck on Windows
request.c: split scan_charset into two functions

Fix pytest finding librecode DLL on Python >= 3.8; require Python >= 3.8

Python 3.8 is the oldest still-supported version as of now, so that’s OK.
GitHub CI: add missing setuptools on macOS; it needs python@3.12
src/task.c: fix a potential NULL dereference (thanks, GCC!)
AUTHORS: remove authors of code no longer in Recode

iconv: fix an infinite loop on invalid/untranslatable input

This bug was introduced in commit 162f24f.

If iconv gives an error, and we do not return with an error ourselves, then
skip a byte (we can’t tell how much we should skip!).

Fix externally-visible APIs in recodext.h

These symbols were automatically prefixed with librecode_ by cleaner.h.
However, the declarations in recodext.h were not altered, so the symbols
declared in recodext.h were not accessible.

Remove the prefix #defines for these symbols from cleaner.h (which now just
contains declarations for module_ and delmodule_ functions, plus one other
that is not public), and instead add a recode_ prefix (for consistency with
other APIs). Also remove some #defines pertaining to defunct functions from
cleaner.h.

src/task.c: only close input stream when we opened it (fix #48)

Thanks to Remi Collet for the bug report and fix.

tests/Makefile.am: fix tests on Windows

Add Recode DLL directory to PATH.

doc/Makefile.am: simplify and fix info generation

No need to specify TEXINFO_TEX, as automake will look in build-aux,
configured with AC_CONFIG_AUX_DIR in configure.ac

Add rfc1345.texi as a dependency of recode.info using recode_TEXINFOS,
rather than with a make rule; in turn, this allows automake to insert the
rule that makes recode.info depend on version.texi.
bootstrap.conf: update gnu.org URL to https scheme
doc/version.texi: remove generated file from git

Use gnulib iconv module

As well as allowing some simplification, this fixes linking on Windows
having used -no-undefined.

Thanks to Bruno Haible for diagnosing the problem and offering the solution.

Use gnulib’s x-to-1 to generate man page

The x-to-1 script avoids problems when help2man is not present, or when
cross-compiling.

Thanks to Bruno Haible for not only writing x-to-1 many years ago, but
adding features specially for recode just now.
.gitignore: remove unnecessary pattern
gnulib: update to get latest x-to-1

src/Makefile.am: librecode_la_LDFLAGS: add -no-undefined

-no-undefined is a libtool requirement to build shared libs on
Windows-based platforms like Cygwin.
src/Makefile.am: remove defunct comment
Update gnulib to fix setlocale on recent Cygwin
tests/setup.py.in: fix Cython C includes path for VPATH build
po: remove generated files
Update version in version.texi and recode.pot
configure.ac: call AC_PROG_LEX with option noyywrap
Bump version to 3.7.14 and add NEWS
Remove pofiles from git; they are in the Translation Project

Copyright notices: make punctuation consistent

Change “Progiciels Bourbeau-Pinard inc.” to “Progiciels Bourbeau-Pinard,
Inc.” (capitalize “Inc” and put a comma before it) as everywhere else.
GitHub CI: don't fetch all commits
GitHub CI: remove unnecessary git autocrlf setting
Switch from AppVeyor CI to GitHub Actions
